The Oak Ridge Electron Linear Accelerator was
operated at a pulse rate of 525 Hz, a pulse width of
8 ns, and a power of 7-8 kW. Neutronnenergy was
determined by time of flight.
The samples were enriched metallic molybdenum.
Capture and transmission samples were 0.004591
and 0.02507 at/b thick, respectively.
Neutron capture measurements were made using a
pair of C6D6 detectors. A 10B filter was used to
remove overlap neutrons from preceding beam bursts,
and a Pb filter was used to reduce gamma flash
effects. Both filters were placed in the beam at a
distance of 5 m from the neutron source.
